OL,3,CNew Zealand PM apologises to 200,000
OL,4,Csurvivors of 'unimaginable' abuse
OL,6,FA report released in July estimated
OL,7,Fmore than 200,000 people in state,
OL,8,Ffoster, and faith-based care in New
OL,9,FZealand suffered severe abuse between
OL,10,F1950 and 2019. Those who suffered were
OL,11,Fdisproportionately Maori, New
OL,12,FZealand's Indigenous people.
OL,14,F"It was horrific. It was
OL,15,Fheartbreaking. It was wrong. And it
OL,16,Fshould never have happened," Luxon
OL,17,Fsaid in New Zealand's Parliament on
OL,18,FTuesday as he spoke to survivors of
OL,19,Fabuse.
