OL,3,CNew Zealand PM apologises to 200,000
OL,4,Csurvivors of 'unimaginable' abuse
OL,6,FHe apologised for the role previous
OL,7,Fgovernments had in the abuse, "For
OL,8,Fmany of you it changed the course of
OL,9,Fyour life, and for that, the
OL,10,Fgovernment must take responsibility".
OL,12,F"Words do matter and I say these words
OL,13,Fwith sincerity: I have read your
OL,14,Fstories, and I believe you."
OL,16,FHe added vulnerable people in foster
OL,17,Fand church care, "should have been
OL,18,Fsafe and treated with respect, dignity
OL,19,Fand compassion... But instead, you
OL,20,Fwere subjected to horrific abuse and
OL,21,Fneglect and in some cases torture".
