OL,3,CNew Zealand PM apologises to 200,000
OL,4,Csurvivors of 'unimaginable' abuse
OL,6,F"Many people entering into state and
OL,7,Ffaith-based institutions were
OL,8,Fundocumented. Records were incomplete,
OL,9,Fthey've gone missing, and in some
OL,10,Fcases, yes, they were deliberately
OL,11,Fdestroyed."
OL,13,FIn response to the findings, New
OL,14,FZealand's government agreed for the
OL,15,Ffirst time that the historical
OL,16,Ftreatment of some children in a
OL,17,Fnotorious state-run hospital amounted
OL,18,Fto torture, and pledged an apology to
OL,19,Fall those abused in state, foster and
OL,20,Freligious care since 1950.
