OL,3,CNew Zealand PM apologises to 200,000
OL,4,Csurvivors of 'unimaginable' abuse
OL,6,FLuxon's government was publicly
OL,7,Fdenounced by some survivors and
OL,8,Fadvocates earlier on Tuesday ahead of
OL,9,Fthe apology - for not yet having
OL,10,Frevealing plans for the financial
OL,11,Fcompensation of those abused.
OL,13,FFa'afete Taito, a survivor of violent
OL,14,Fabuse at another state-run home, said
OL,15,Fthe apology was "not enough".
OL,17,F"It's not enough to say sorry," he
OL,18,Fsaid.
